lenders.name: Teddy
lenders.loan_because:
I feel like it is my duty to help others.  My mother had fourteen children, was divorced, had two jobs, and went to a trade school.  Her entire life, struggled immensely, but still somehow found a way to help an innumerable amount of people in need - even though she herself was in need.  She was a maid in 1950s and 1960s California, and had to face racism and sexism; in spite this, still helped men, women, and children of all races, nationalities, and creeds.  She taught her children to be altruistic, and I in turn have taught this to my children.  I too am a divorcee, and feel like I now have a fresh start.  In fact I feel like every single day is a fresh start.  I would like everyone to be able to feel that magical sensation of a fresh start.  Though these loans are only $25.00, I hope that whoever gets the loan will utilize it not only in founding a business or whatever their endeavors, but also in obtaining a genuine fresh start.  Even though I cannot help as many people as I would like, through this Kiva program, I can reuse the loans so that by helping one person, I would eventually be helping a multitude of people.  And just as my mother has taught the importance of giving to me, and I have taught it to my children, I know full well that those that I help will in turn help others in the world.  It is the natural thing to do.  It's beautiful to see all of these people here wanting to help others, and it's definitely what we need in this world of greed and selfishness that we live in today.

"I should like to help everyone if possible; Jew, Gentile, black [people], white. We all want to help one another. Human beings are like that. We want to live by each other's happiness, not by each other's misery. We don't want to hate and despise one another. In this world there is room for everyone. And the good earth is rich and can provide for everyone. The way of life can be free and beautiful, but we have lost the way."
~ Charlie Chaplin as The Great Dictator
